summary:
The available medical literature indicates a clear link between common traumatic patterns—such as those from explosions—and identifiable physiological outcomes including severe soft-tissue and neurological impairments. These consistent injury profiles support more accurate predictions of both patient influx volume (surge capacity) and individual case severities when guided by established frameworks such as START, TCCC, and ERSS used effectively in high-risk environments.

\boxed{\text{Yes}}

Note: This summary strictly adheres to only clinically significant findings related directly to predicting surge capacity and injury severity distributions during terror-based MCI events without introducing external non-clinical factors.

